      <description>There are two components to &amp;#8220;Fat, Sick and Nearly Dead,&amp;#8221; &amp;#8211; the film, which chronicles Joe Cross&amp;#8217; journey to health via juicing and the website and juicing/health program called &amp;#8220;Reboot Your Life.&amp;#8221; Fat, Sick and Nearly Dead is a great documentary, dubbed the &amp;#8220;juice cleanse movie&amp;#8221; by some, but it&amp;#8217;s catchy title doesn&amp;#8217;t give enough [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/juice-cleanse/Juice_Cleanse-Fat_Sick_and_Nearly_Dead-_Review.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>There are two components to &#8220;Fat, Sick and Nearly Dead,&#8221; &#8211; the film, which chronicles Joe Cross&#8217; journey to health via juicing and the website and juicing/health program called &#8220;<a href="http://www.juicecleansenow.com/juice-fast/juice-fast-has-fans-skeptics/">Reboot Your Life</a>.&#8221;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B004V4ASGC/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=juicecleansenow-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B004V4ASGC"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-1663" title="Fat, Sick &amp; Nearly Dead" src="http://www.juicecleansenow.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Screen-shot-2011-08-04-at-7.52.49-PM.png" alt="Fat, Sick And Nearly Dead: Review" width="215" height="333" /></a><em>Fat, Sick and Nearly Dead</em> is a great documentary, dubbed the &#8220;juice cleanse movie&#8221; by some, but it&#8217;s catchy title doesn&#8217;t give enough credit to the depth of the journey Joe Cross goes on in the film. It&#8217;s one that I found incredibly inspiring and motivating.</p>
<p>Kind of like the reverse &#8220;Super Size Me,&#8221; instead of getting unhealthier, Joe gets healthier. He meets people, talks to them about their diets, and even helps some along the way adopt a healthier way of life for themselves.</p>
<p>What I found most refreshing about the movie was that it wasn&#8217;t preachy. Even if you&#8217;re not interested in going all raw and juicing for 0 days like Cross, you&#8217;ll still enjoy the movie immensely. It&#8217;s not just about the food, it&#8217;s about the people and the journey too.</p>
<p>Cross lost 100 pounds during his 60 day journey. That&#8217;s a LONG juice cleanse!</p>
<p><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B004V4ASGC/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=juicecleansenow-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B004V4ASGC">Click here to watch</a> <em>Fat, Sick and Nearly Dead</em>.<br />
<small><br />
</small></p>
