      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="Juice Party!" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/43139087@N00/5443453176/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2268" title="5443453176_b343f3ab77" src="http://www.juicecleansenow.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/5443453176_b343f3ab77.jpg" alt="Juice Fast" width="500" height="374" /></a><br />
If you are looking for an effective method of cleansing your whole system or cutting weight, a juice fast can be your answered prayer. Juice fasting, in other words, is considered a form of detoxification.</p>
<p>It involves the intake of fruit juices and raw vegetables, or just water. Fruit juices and raw vegetables are the proponents of an effective juice fast because they are good sources of antioxidants and rich in vitamins and minerals. Organic fruits and vegetables will be the most beneficial for you as they won&#8217;t introduce any new toxins or heavy metals into your system. Green, leafy vegetables are advised as good and beneficial during the fasting.</p>
<p>But not all kinds of fruits and their parts are recommended for detoxification juice fasting.  Avoid:</p>
<ul>
<li>pits of cherries</li>
<li>apple seeds</li>
<li>tough skin of pineapples</li>
</ul>
<p>And because no solid food is eaten, juice fast can be considered as quick and easy way to be cleansed and detoxified.</p>
<p>People undergo juice fast in order to loss weight, to help themselves quit unhealthy habits such as drug addiction, smoking or alcoholism, or due to religious reasons. Some believe that juice fast can alter some medical practices like treating pain, depression, and other diseases.</p>
<p>You shouldn&#8217;t attempt a juice fast or cleanse if you are:</p>
<ul>
<li>a pregnant women</li>
<li>sick children</li>
<li>anyone with a chronic condition</li>
<li>patients undergoing undergone surgical procedures (because juice fast is capable of reducing proteins in the blood and can interfere with medications).</li>
</ul>
<div>If you&#8217;re concerned, always ask your doctor before attempting any kind of nutritional changes.</div>
<p>While juice fast helps to quickly cleanse the body, it can also result to possible side effects. Side effects of juice fast may involve:</p>
<ul>
<li>headaches</li>
<li>weight loss (YAY!)</li>
<li>dehydration and electrolyte loss caused by diarrhea</li>
<li>headaches</li>
</ul>
<p>If side effects become worse and symptoms of particular disease or disorder occur, the faster is advised to immediately consult a doctor for further examinations. Diabetes is one major disease juice fasting can bring. Furthermore, dieticians agreed that fasting is less effective than drinking plenty of water, and that it can be habitual especially to those who use fasting as weight loss treatment. It is all because of the obsession of not gaining weight and maintaining their thin and slim bodies through the method of juice fast.</p>
<p>A beginner juice fast usually lasts for a short-term period like one to three days. Any juice fast requires juice! THe easiest way to get fresh, organic, healthy juice is with a juicer. Here are a few of the top juicers on Amazon:</p>
