      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.juicecleansenow.com/?p=160</guid>
      <description>Fresh apple juice direct from the tree will always be the best for an apple juice cleanse &amp;#8211; like most juice cleanses you want organic, fresh produce to ensure you&amp;#8217;re not adding any toxins to your body while you&amp;#8217;re trying to expel them! It&amp;#8217;s also recommended that the apple juice you use for your apple [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/juice-cleanse/Juice_Cleanse-Apple_Juice_Cleanse.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="Fresh pressed apple juice" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/60364452@N00/3019331462/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3204/3019331462_e24f505a46_m.jpg" alt="Apple Juice Cleanse" border="0" title="Apple Juice Cleanse Pic" /></a>Fresh apple juice direct from the tree will always be the best for an apple juice cleanse &#8211; like most juice cleanses you want organic, fresh produce to ensure you&#8217;re not adding any toxins to your body while you&#8217;re trying to expel them!</p>
<p>It&#8217;s also recommended that the apple juice you use for your apple juice cleanse be unfiltered. That fiber is good for you! Many folks add prune juice to an apple juice cleanse to avoid constipation, and also alternate glasses of water with the thick, unfiltered apple juice.</p>
<p>You can add a tablespoon of lemon juice to the apple juice if desired for a taste change and for the liver cleansing effects lemon juice is said to have.</p>
