      <description>A 3 day juice cleanse is a more feasable option for most of us who are new to juice fasting and fasting. We can get our toes wet and see if we like it. With a juice cleanse, you&amp;#8217;ll only be eating raw fruit and vegetables. Some people believe that in doing so, you&amp;#8217;ll detox [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/juice-cleanse/Juice_Cleanse-3_Day_Juice_Cleanses.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="Kiwi" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/68318414@N00/5928761055/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm7.static.flickr.com/6150/5928761055_cab80f622c.jpg" alt="3 Day Juice Cleanses" border="0" title="3 Day Juice Cleanses Pic" /></a><br />
A 3 day juice cleanse is a more feasable option for most of us who are new to juice fasting and fasting. We can get our toes wet and see if we like it. With a juice cleanse, you&#8217;ll only be eating raw fruit and vegetables. Some people believe that in doing so, you&#8217;ll detox your body as well, since it doesn&#8217;t have to work as hard digesting the raw juices. Aside from any potential detoxification benefits, a juice fast, being entirely made up of fruits and vegetables, is very rich in vitamins, minerals and antioxidants.</p>
<p><strong><em>It&#8217;s not a bad idea to attempt your first 3 day juice cleanse on a holiday or 3 day weekend, if you work outside the home.</em></strong></p>
<p>During your 3 day juice cleanse, it&#8217;s recommended you consume a minimum of 32 to 64 ounces of vegetable and fruit juice each day. You can juice your materials at home if you have a juicer, or you can purchase your juices ahead of time. If you buy your juice, make sure it&#8217;s 100% raw fruit and/or veggie juice with no additives.</p>
<p>Some favorites for a 3 day juice cleanse:</p>
<ul>
<li>Pineapples</li>
<li>Cranberries</li>
<li>Kale</li>
<li>Carrots</li>
<li>Cabbage</li>
<li>Beets</li>
<li>Apples</li>
<li>Spinach</li>
</ul>
<p>Having been on juice only for 3 days, when you&#8217;re done with your cleanse make sure you introduce your body back to solid and cooked foods in a gradual fashion, so as not to shock your digestive system. You can start with eating raw, unjuiced fruit or steamed vegetables. Plain foods like salad, rice or crackers are a good follow up if your body handles the first solids well.</p>
<p>The easiest way to continue juicing as a lifelong habit for heath and not just a one-off &#8220;cleanse&#8221; or weight loss tool is by owning your own juicer. Here are a few of the most popular juicers for your 3 day juice cleanse and beyond:</p>
